  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-01 orphan claim)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. A primary claim asserting hemolysis index acceptability is bound to this UoA; the claim is supported in prose by extensive simulation campaigns but lacks a structured prov:wasDerivedFrom link to any Evidence node, constituting an orphan claim (W-EP-01).",
